DPRK Delegate Refers to Peaceful Use of Space 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- The Democratic People's Republic of Korea will positively promote the cooperation and exchange with the international community including the UN and different countries of the world and develop the independent space science and technology in the field of peaceful use of the space.
 A DPRK delegate said this in his speech during the discussion on the agenda item "The international cooperation in the peaceful use of the space" at the meeting of the 4th committee of the 60th UN General Assembly on Oct. 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that the space should not become someone's monopoly, adding that if the universe is to become a peaceful one conducive to promoting the welfare of humankind it is important to reject the monopolistic practices in the space development and enable all countries to freely participate in it on an equal footing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The successes achieved in the space development should be shared for the well-being of all countries and peoples. It is necessary to categorically reject any attempt to disturb and control the developing countries' activities for the space development and monopolize the space in a bid to retain a technological edge. 
 It is also necessary to stand firm against any attempt to militarize the space if it is to become a peaceful one conducive to the well-being of mankind.
 The DPRK assails all moves to turn the space into a military base and battle site against the sovereign states and calls for building an international legal mechanism for preventing the space militarization as early as possible, he asserted.

Birthday of WPK Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- Meetings and film shows were held in Sofia, Vienna and Quito in the period from Oct. 3 to 7 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Participants of the film shows watched Korean films including "The Brilliant History of the Great Leadership" and "'Ever-Victorious Workers' Party of Korea', Grand Gymnastic and Artistic Performance for Celebrating the 55th Anniversary of the WPK." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Milcho Gyuvrov, vice-chairman of the Bulgaria-Korea Friendship Association, and Vasilka Nikiforova, chief of the   Kim Il Sung Library in Sofia, said that the organizational and ideological basis for party founding was laid under the wise leadership of Kim Il Sung and since its foundation the WPK has creditably performed its mission and role as a guiding force of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Erich Zavadil, general secretary of the Society for the Promotion of the Relations between Austria and the DPRK, said that the DPRK has dynamically pushed forward the building of a great prosperous powerful nation under the wise leadership of   Kim Jong Il, weathering out all trials that resulted from the political and military pressure and economic sanctions of the U.S.-led imperialist allied forces and repeated natural disasters.
 Victor Granda, chairman of the Socialist Party of Ecuador, noted: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foundation of the WPK brought a decisive turn in carving out the destiny of the Korean people. The 60 year-long history of the WPK is precisely the history of the tireless revolutionary activities of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. That's why the history of the WPK is shining as a glorious one as it has performed great exploits in the course of traversing a most right and unique path. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings held in Bulgaria and Austria.

Polish Diplomats Help Korean Farmers in Harvesting 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- Polish Ambassador to the DPRK Roman Iwaszkiewicz and embassy officials Wednesday gave helping hands to the farmers of the DPRK-Poland Friendship Jangsuwon Co-op Farm on the outskirts of Pyongyang, in carrying rice sheaves.
 After looking round the room devoted to the farm's history, the guests watched an art performance given by kindergarteners of the farm and conversed with officials of the farm, deepening the friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ambassador said that he would strive hard to boost the long-standing friendly and cooperative relations between Poland and the DPRK and wished the farmers greater success in their current farm work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They conveyed aid materials carrying their sincerity to the farm that day.

Agreement of S. Korea-U.S. Security Consultative Council Meeting Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly made public a statement titled "We denounce an agreement of the south Korea-U.S annual security consultative council meeting denying the joint statement of the six-party talks" on Oct. 22.
 The statement referred to the fact that it was agreed at the 37th security consultative council meeting that the U.S. would sustain the provision of "nuclear umbrella" to south Korea and keep the U.S. forces and the UNC stationed. This is a dangerous agreement wholly denying the joint statement of the six-party talks which confirmed that the U.S. has no intention to attack and invade the north with nuclear or conventional weapons, the statement said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the council meeting it was also agreed to reaffirm that the "successful completion of the transfer of the U.S. military bases in south Korea is a cornerstone of future south Korea-U.S. alliance" and the strategic flexibility of the U.S. forces is of sustained importance. It is a humiliating and subordinate war agreement which further strengthens the south Korea-U.S. alliance and harms peace in the Korean Peninsula. 
 With the joint statement of the six-party talks the U.S. troops have lost any justification for their presence in this land. The U.S. should take a substantial measure for building a permanent peace system in the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government authorities should not follow the U.S. war moves, bound to the south Korea-U.S. alliance, a war alliance, but take the road of national cooperation for peace and reunification of the Korean Peninsula.

Withdrawal of U.S. Troops from S. Korea Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- It is essential for ensuring security on the Korean Peninsula to drive the U.S. troops out of south Korea. 
 Minju Joson Thursday says this in a signed commentary refuting the accusation made against the DPRK at the 37th meeting of the "security consultative council" held between south Korea and the U.S. in Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By pulling up others, while keeping mum about their arms build-up the United States and the south Korean authorities seek a sinister aim. This diatribe is aimed at misleading the public opinion with the fifth six-party talks just around the corner in a bid to impair the international dignity of the DPRK, pressurize it and invent a pretext for starting a war of aggression against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Solutions to the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula, the issue of security and the issue of Korea's reunification depend on the settlement of the fundamental issue, ie the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The actions of the Korean nation and other people of the world for the pullback of the U.S. troops from south Korea will mount higher as long as the United States and the south Korean authorities turn their faces away from the fundamental issue of guaranteeing peace on the Korean Peninsula.  
 The U.S. would be well advised to drop its unrealizable ambition to seize the DPRK by force of arms and take a bold decision to pull all its armed forces out of south Korea as early as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities should urge the United States to drop its policy of aggression against the north and withdraw from south Korea its forces, the cancer-like existence disturbing peace and the movement for reunification as unanimously demanded by the Korean nation. They should bear in mind that their talk about "self-reliant national defence," dodging the issue of the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea, is a criminal act little short of deceiving and insulting the fellow countrymen all out in the grand march for independent reunification under the banner of "By our nation itself".

National Symposium on Medical Science Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- A national symposium on medical science was held here from Oct. 24 to 26 to mark the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. It was sponsored by the Central Committee of the Korean Medical Association. 
 Attending the symposium were officials concerned and scientists and researchers in the field of medical science from across the country. 
 Chairman of the Central Committee of the KMA Choe Chang Sik presented his paper titled "The WPK, great mother party that has set a brilliant worldwide example in solving the issue of public health of the working people." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il comprehensively formulated and systematized the essence and mission of the Juche-oriented public health and its tasks and ways, etc, thus clearly indicating the way for the public health to follow in its development and wisely leading it in each period and at every stage of revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need for all the officials, scientists and researchers in the field of public health to bring about fresh innovation in the preventive and curative medical care and medical science researches true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of the Party and thus positively contribute to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The symposium was divided into the panels of surgery, internal medicine, Koryo medicine, sanitation and anti-epidemic science, pharmacology and basic medical science. The symposium heard at least 330 papers on the successes made in medical science through the efforts to implement the Party's policy on public health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Drawing particular attention of the participants were the paper "Research into the great vessel disease and the method of treating its trouble" presented by Kim Hyong Jik Military Medical University, the paper "On making Korean traditional Saengmaek tea and its pharmacological effect" by the Academy of Koryo Medicine, the paper "Research into the manufacture of anticancer agent out of bark of maackia amurensis" by the Pharmaceutical Institute of the Academy of Medical Science and other papers.

International Commodity Exhibition Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- The First Autumn International Commodity Exhibition has been successfully held from October 24 to 27 in Pyongyang under the sponsorship of the Korean International Exhibition Corporation.
  Over ten trade corporations of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and 78 companies from different countries including China, Netherlands, Romania, Switzerland, Sweden and Italy and regions participated in the exhibition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  On display there were more than 20,000 pieces of  5,000 kinds of goods including ironware, machine tools, poultry facilities, medicines, agricultural chemicals and fertilizers, petrol chemical goods, electric and electronic goods and foodstuffs and technical data. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Particularly, wire cut electro-discharge machine, digital combined vertical processing lathe and NC lathe, mining machines and poultry facilities attracted the attention of the visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the exhibition, delegates of enterprises had wide range of contacts to explore possibilities of trade transactions and concluded commodity export contracts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It contributed to the development of economic cooperation and exchange between countries.

Anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's On-Spot-Guidance to Changdok School Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- A meeting took place at the Changdok School Thursday to celebrate the 60th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's on-the-spot guidance to the school. 
 The Changdok School is associated with his immortal revolutionary history in which he studied there with a great will for revolution from April, Juche 12 (1923) to Juche 14 (1925). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After Korean liberation the President visited his alma mater on Oct. 28, Juche 34 (1945) and clearly indicated the way to be followed by the country's democratic education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the visit he underscored the need to train native cadres needed for building a new country by the efforts of the Korean people, adding that the teachers should properly understand the reality of the country and work heart and soul for the education of the rising generation. 
 In the subsequent period, too, he visited there several times and called for firmly establishing Juche in education to help pupils study well everything Korean, among other things, and intensify the class education among them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the instructions given by Kim Il Sung during his on-the-spot guidance and leader Kim Jong Il's deep care the school has been equipped with a variety of modern educational facilities and has trained its pupils as fine scientists and technicians for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. 
 Kang Jun Ho, principal of the school, in a report recalled the successes made in the past by firmly establishing Juche in education and stressed the need to grow its pupils to be fine scientists and technicians truly conducive to building a great prosperous powerful nation.

19th Symposium on Yun I Sang Music Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- The 19th symposium on Yun I Sang music was held at the People's Palace of Culture Thursday. 
 Present there were Choe Chang Il, vice-minister of Culture, Ri Il Nam, director of the Yun I Sang Music Institute, officials concerned, creators, researchers and artistes in the field of culture and arts.
 Among those present there were the widow and daughter of Yun, a delegation of the south Korean "Yun I Sang Peace Foundation" led by its Director Sin Kye Ryun, national assemblyman from the Uri Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
At the symposium Master of Music Ho Chang Hwal, researcher of the Yun I Sang Music Institute, spoke on the subject "On a number of features of methods of expression in Yun I Sang's polyphonic music," Ri Son Yong, researcher of the institute, on the subject of "Study of Yun I Sang's music created before the middle of the 1950s," Prof. and Master of Music Kang Yong Gol, teacher of Pyongyang University of Music and Dance, on the subject of "On diverse and peculiar methods of expression and rendition in case of Yun I Sang's music" and Kim Song Ryul, room chief of the institute on the subject "Study of quartet of Yun I Sang's string music." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They explained and proved the ideas and contents of music pieces composed by Yun and his peculiar methods of musical composition, etc., and spoke highly of creative activities dedicated to national reconciliation and unity and the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The symposium provided an opportunity to analyze and prove in depth the achievements made by Yun's music and their worth and contributed to deepening the understanding of his patriotic music world.
